For the crayfish, bring 4 litres/7 pints water to the boil. Add the stout, salt, sugar, dill crowns and anise seeds. Add all the crayfish, bring back to the boil and boil for between 8-10 minutes. Strain and allow to cool before eating.For the truffle butter, melt the butter and whisk in the truffle oil. Season with a little salt.  Taste to make sure the truffle flavour is pronounced enough, adjust as necessary.Serve the crayfish with the melted truffle butter alongside.